          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              My initial impression is utter horror that the journals no longer have their own space on the right hand side (which is an empty void if you scroll down past the first page) showing a bunch of the latest articles.<BR><BR>They seem to be lumped in with all the main stories... or underneath them - it's unclear whether they will always be way down the bottom or will move nearer the top when updated. In any case it seems there is no way to see the most recent dozen (or so) journal entries like you previously could on the main page, and now have to go digging through a maze of similar looking posts to get to them... well, unless I scroll down about 50 pages right to the bottom of the site.<BR><BR>Seems very disorganised to me, with everything shoved together into one big jumble.<BR><BR><BR>Less content in more space :/

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
